"""5-method registration comparison using watershed HCR binarisation.

Methods (all initialised by the same FFT-NCC θ-sweep rigid stage):

  M1 rigid               — translation + rotation only.
  M2 rigid + affine      — 4-DOF similarity (Powell on -NCC), uniform
                           scale cap ±15 %, rotation cap ±15°.
  M3 rigid + coarse Bspl — M2 affine then coarse BSpline (mesh=6,
                           multi-resolution, displacement-field
                           smoothed σ=4 px).
  M4 rigid + PWR (binary)— Suite2p-style piecewise rigid on binary
                           masks (4×4 grid, per-block NCC sweep,
                           Gaussian-smoothed displacement field).
  M5 rigid + PWR (intens)— same 4×4 PWR but fixed = HCR 488 raw MIP
                           (log-normalised) and moving = blurred CZ
                           binary (σ=2 µm) — uses image intensity
                           instead of binary masks.

HCR target uses the watershed binarisation (`compare_binarization`'s
``variant_watershed``) — the comparison run from 2026-04-26 showed it
splits touching cells the best while preserving fill fraction.

Outputs:
  • figures/compare_methods_watershed_{sid}.png — 2×3 panel per subject
  • figures/compare_methods_watershed_summary.png — bar chart
  • compare_methods_watershed_summary.json
"""
